Author | first business | android

Finally, at a little after 10:00 a.m. on Feb. 4, Liu Wen (not his real name) of Hankou, Wuhan, took an ambulance to Huoshenshan hospital on the 11th day of his fever and the 6th day after his admission.

At Vulcan Mountain Hospital, he was still struggling with his illness, but his heart was full of hope. He made several videos and posted them on the doubler. In the video, Liu said, coughing and gasping, the conditions here are better than I could have imagined.

At the end of January, Liu Wen, who was suffering from a persistent high fever, was isolated at home and helped himself. His mood remained calm and restrained, but as his illness worsened, his family members began to show symptoms of fever, let Liu Wen made no matter what will be admitted to hospital treatment of the decision.

This newspaper published on January 28 Liu Wen's experience Article "a suspected new crown patient's self-help: changing the prescription to take medicine, through the room door to chat" received great attention. "I must recover as soon as possible and give confidence to everyone who cares about me, " Liu said

The experience of the past few days has turned Liu Wen into a particularly prone to tears. "I am a man in my 40s, and I have been crying more than I have in the past few decades. "

The hospital had not mentioned the cost to him since he was hospitalized on January 31. "The state bears the cost, not empty words, thanks the state, " he said.

As of 2400 hours on February 4, the National Health Commission had received 24,324 confirmed cases from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, according to the National Health Commission's official website, there are 3219 severe cases, 490 death cases, 892 cured cases (1 case each in Hainan and Hubei provinces) , and 23260 suspected cases. A total of 252154 close contacts have been traced, 18,457 people were released from medical observation on the same day, and 185555 people are currently under medical observation.

Admitted

For several days, Liu Wen (not his real name)'s body temperature fluctuated under the influence of drugs, making him feel as if he were in a The Perfect Storm. "I, for one, never eat chicken, but for the sake of my energy, I tried to resist eating chicken noodle soup. It was terrible to get sick, and I began to throw up everything I ate, " Liu said.

With the fever getting worse, Liu Wen felt he would have to be hospitalized anyway. On the morning of January 30, Liu Wen decided to give it a try after hearing that a new ward with 700 beds had been opened in the western district of the Union Hospital. In the morning, Liu Wen dragged his sick body and drove dozens of kilometers, but was stopped by the police near the Union hospital because there was no pass when the whole city was forbidden to travel and he had a fever, so he had to turn back.

In the afternoon, a friend told Liu Wen that new wards had been opened at the Wuhan Center Hospital, and there were beds. Liu Wen quickly went to the Wuhan Center Hospital again. This time he was admitted smoothly, "after being admitted to the hospital, I found that I was in a hurry and didn't take anything with me. Even the toilet paper was bought the next day by running errands, " Liu said.

That night, Liu Wen's wife called him, the bad news is, their daughter is also in a fever. At that moment, Liu Wen felt his heart is about to be broken, but he was helpless in the face of illness, can only strive to make their own recovery as soon as possible.

"That night, I slept very badly, more than two o'clock in the morning, and suddenly had a sharp pain in my lungs and woke up. " Liu Wen said that he had been wearing an N95 mask since he left home, plus he had difficulty breathing. Liu Wen felt that, it's a luxury.

At 5:30 am on January 31, Liu Wen was woken up by a nurse to have blood drawn and a throat swab tested. High Fever and vomiting in recent days have weakened Liu Wen's physique and made it difficult to find blood vessels. From Elbow, back of hand to foot, barely managed to scrape together six tubes of blood. The nurse still gave Liu Wen to stick indwelling needle, drop on the first bottle of medicine. The nurse said there was a shortage of medicine because of the large number of patients.

At 8:30 in the morning, the hospital delivered breakfast, which surprised Liu Wen, he thought the hospital has no time to take care of food, he can only live on biscuits, did not expect breakfast: Meat Dumplings, porridge, boiled eggs. Though he always wanted to vomit, Liu Wen swallowed his breakfast in one gulp. Because he knew that only when he was full, his body had the strength to fight the virus.

On the same day, Liu's mother, a 70-year-old man, arrived at the hospital after more than an hour's walk, stood in line for two hours to get tested, had a double lung infection, a highly suspected case, and started receiving injections.

Liu Wen's wife is also in bad shape. She also has a high fever for several days, but she can only keep it up at home because no one wants to take their daughter. The little girl is only 9 years old and can not be left alone.

Transfer to another hospital

Liu's temperature has hovered around 38 degrees since he was admitted to the hospital, especially since it spiked to 39 degrees on the afternoon of Feb. 1. From the abdominal muscles to the sternum, due to a severe cough, "The most serious thing is that physical pain can interfere with eating. Every bite of food hurts for more than a minute. It's really all you can do. You've been eating for almost half an hour and you've only had a small bite. But I had to eat and drink as much as I could in order to get out of the hospital and go home as soon as possible,"Liu said.

This Day, outside began to buy Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, because the day before, there is news that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid can resist the virus. "I was really moved that my friend went straight to grab it and wanted to send it to me. But the reality is, the courier service doesn't work, " Liu said.

On February 2, Liu Wen's temperature had risen above 39 degrees, or 90 percent, Oxygenation. On January 26, the third day of his fever, Oxygenation was normal.

The head of the smoking department came to see me in the morning and told me that the disease usually peaked on the 10th day and that I had to hold on and that they would give me hormones to help me get through this difficult period. Once it's over, day 14, it's pretty much over. Of course, if it gets any worse at that time, we'll have to start rescuing it,"Liu said.

Liu Wen in the hospital when the treatment, outside this time also sent the good news: Liu Wen's wife has been reduced fever, the child also no longer has a fever, especially the mother also began to reduce fever. "I couldn't stop crying as long as they got over it, " Liu said.

On February 3rd, everything was moving in a better direction. That day, the good news came one after another. First, the previous day's hormone therapy had worked, Liu's fever had subsided, and Oxygenation was back to normal.

"In the morning, the doctors also informed me that I might be sent to the Vulcan Mountain Hospital. The military doctors are looking at my information and approving it, and once they are sure, they will send me there in the afternoon. I should be lucky, " Liu said.

On this day, though no longer feverish, Liu's mother was moved by the community to a unified quarantine point, a newly built but not yet open hotel, commandeered by the government, one room each, in good condition. His wife was also told to go to the community for a nucleic acid test.

Finally, at 10:00 am on February 4, the 11th day of Liu Wen's fever, the 6th day after he was admitted to the hospital, he boarded the ambulance to go to the Fire God Mountain Hospital, to the Fire God Mountain Hospital. The best hospitals, the best equipment and the best doctors, says Liu, who feels he will soon be cured.
